    <item>
      <title>Pyramid Fractal</title>
      <link>http://bluevisual.tv/personal/pyramidfractal/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 02 Jan 2013 10:38:25 -0400</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://bluevisual.tv/personal/pyramidfractal/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve always been interested in mathematics, which led to an early interest in fractals, which are mathematical self-similar shapes and formulas. A well-known one is the Mandelbrot fractal. A key characteristic of fractals is that if you look at a smaller part of the whole, you will see the same same structures at completely different scales.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;project-image&#34; oncontextmenu=&#34;return false;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;label for=&#34;lightbox-toggle1&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://bluevisual.tv/images/pyramidfractal-01.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/label&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;input type=&#34;checkbox&#34; name=&#34;lightbox-toggle1&#34; id=&#34;lightbox-toggle1&#34; /&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;lightbox&#34; oncontextmenu=&#34;return false;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;label for=&#34;lightbox-toggle1&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://bluevisual.tv/images/pyramidfractal-01.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/label&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;project-image&#34; oncontextmenu=&#34;return false;&#34;&gt;
